of Dr. Joe S. Green, "The Bayou Bishop"
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the Legislature of Louisiana on the death of Dr. Joe S. Green,
3 "The Bayou Bishop".
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the Legislature of
5 Louisiana has learned of the passing, on February 20, 2026, of Dr. Joe S. Green, "The Bayou
6 Bishop"; and
7 WHEREAS, Joe S. Green was born on May 20, 1940, in Pineville, Louisiana, to
8 Henry Green, Sr., and Ada Morris Green and grew up as a farm boy along Bayou Rapides;
9 and
10 WHEREAS, in his youth, Joe was active in many activities and ministries in the
11 church and community; he was a regular attendee at First Evening Star Baptist Church, and
12 in 1949, he accepted Christ on Good Friday and was baptized on Easter Sunday by the late
13 Reverend Luke Williams; and
14 WHEREAS, Joe began his educational journey at Morning Star School, which was
15 housed in Pilgrim Rest Baptist Church; he graduated from Peabody High School in 1958 and
16 continued his education at Southern University in Baton Rouge, United Theological
17 Seminary and Bible College, and Dominican College in Racine, Wisconsin; he held
18 numerous degrees, including a bachelor of theology, master of religion, master of theology,
19 and doctorate of divinity; and
