1 WHEREAS, Joe participated in the Army ROTC during his time at Southern; two
2 years after his enrollment, he was drafted into the military and joined the Special Forces in
3 the 82nd Airborne Division; he retired from the military after twenty-six years of active duty
4 and reserve service; and
5 WHEREAS, Joe married his high school sweetheart, Josephine Reed Green, on
6 October 1, 1962; their union was blessed with three children, and they built a family with
7 values rooted in love and faith; and
8 WHEREAS, Joe accepted the call to ministry while serving as a deacon at Second
9 Evening Star Baptist Church in Boyce, Louisiana, and delivered his first sermon to a
10 congregation of over seven hundred people at the church on Sunday, January 31, 1982; the
11 next week, he accepted the call to serve as pastor of St. Thomas Missionary Baptist Church
12 in Boyce and served there for one year; and
13 WHEREAS, Dr. Green began serving as pastor of St. Matthew Baptist Church in
14 Rapides Parish in February 1983; he served the church for three decades, during which the
15 congregation grew from fifty members to more than one thousand two hundred members;
16 during his tenure he founded Rapides Station Community Ministries, Inc., and C&J Learning
17 and Enrichment Center; he also supported the development of low-income housing for
18 qualified first-time home buyers throughout Louisiana; and
19 WHEREAS, prior to serving as pastor St. Matthew Baptist Church, Dr. Green
20 worked as a job recruiter and trainer for the United States Department of Labor, where he
21 helped develop the Red River waterway; and
22 WHEREAS, Dr. Green's religious affiliations included the National Baptist
23 Convention of America, Louisiana Home & Foreign Mission, Baptist State Convention,
24 United Theological Seminary and Bible College, and United Educational Missionary Baptist
25 Association; he also served as president of the Minister of Economic Development; and
26 WHEREAS, Dr. Joe S. Green is survived by his daughters, Janice Green Washington
27 (Sam), Jacquelyn Green Harris, and Jennifer Green Williams (Darrell); grandchildren, Janeé
28 Green, Javaris Cooper (Lauren), Morgan Cooper Harris (Micheal Jr.), Demetrius Jackson,
29 Shundrial Jackson, Samantha Washington, Salisa Washington, and Evan Clark; great-
30 grandchildren, Jayla Brown, Jaiden Veales, and Jamari Veales; sisters-in-law, Dorothy
